<h3>1. Project Status & Progress</h3>
<p><strong>Brief summary of progress since MVP:</strong><br>
Since the MVP, we finally got the ML models fully talking to our backend. We swapped out the mock data for actual X-ray processing via FastAPI. MongoDB is now fully hooked up to store patient records and analysis history, and the Angular frontend properly uses JWTs to keep everything secure. We also spent a good amount of time fixing the model cold-start delay.</p>

<p><strong>Estimated % completion:</strong> ~85%</p>

<p><strong>Key milestones achieved:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Deployed Faster R-CNN for bounding box rendering on the backend.</li>
    <li>Finished patient CRUD operations and the frontend dashboard visualizations.</li>
    <li>Built a Singleton Warmup for the AI service so the model stays in RAM.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Evidence:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>GitHub commits & PRs for the backend/frontend integration (e.g., PR #58, #60).</li>
    <li>Screenshots of the X-ray result page showing the rendered boxes and confidence scores.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Risks / Delays:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>We ran into a memory spike issue when trying to load multiple models at once, which pushed back our load testing schedule a bit. We're looking into Dockerizing the app soon to cap resource usage.</li>
</ul>

