<h4>4.2 Testing Depth</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Edge cases tested:</strong> We tested uploading corrupted images, files larger than 10MB, and trying to access patient records without a valid JWT token.</li>
    <li><strong>Failure scenarios:</strong> We simulated MongoDB timeouts and inference crashes to make sure the backend throws a clean 500 error instead of hanging the UI.</li>
    <li><strong>Example inputs/outputs:</strong><br>
        <em>Input:</em> Raw chest X-ray image (.jpg).<br>
        <em>Output:</em> Rendered image with bounding boxes drawn over pneumonia regions, returning a JSON response with an 85% confidence score.
    </li>
</ul>

<h4>4.3 Bugs & Issues</h4>
<table>
    <tr>
        <th>Bug ID</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Severity</th>
        <th>Status</th>
        <th>Fix</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>B1</td>
        <td>Model took ~15s to load on every request</td>
        <td>High</td>
        <td>Fixed</td>
        <td>Implemented a Singleton Warmup so it stays in RAM</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>B2</td>
        <td>AI drew multiple overlapping boxes on the same spot</td>
        <td>Medium</td>
        <td>Fixed</td>
        <td>Added Non-Maximum Suppression (NMS) logic</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>B3</td>
        <td>Frontend lost patient context on page refresh</td>
        <td>High</td>
        <td>Fixed</td>
        <td>Updated Angular analysis-state service to persist data</td>
    </tr>
</table>

<h4>4.4 Fix Validation</h4>
<p>For the model loading issue (B1), we ran the backend locally using uvicorn and timed the requests. The first request took about 6 seconds, but everything after that dropped to around 200ms. For the overlapping boxes (B2), we visually checked the fix by running our inference_smoke.py script before and after applying the NMS fix to compare outputs.</p>

